Vancouver Canucks (1-1-1, third in the Pacific) vs. Buffalo Sabres (2-0-0, second in the Atlantic)
Buffalo, New York; Tuesday, 7 p.m. EDT
FANDUEL SPORTSBOOK
 LINE: Sabres +118, Canucks -143; over/under is 6
BOTTOM LINE: The Vancouver Canucks visit Buffalo after the Sabres defeated Arizona 2-1 in a shootout.
Buffalo went 15-34-7 overall with an 8-16-4 record at home during the 2020-21 season. Goalies for the Sabres did not record a shutout last season while compiling an .896 save percentage.
Vancouver went 23-29-4 overall and 10-17-1 on the road in the 2020-21 season. The Canucks scored 148 total goals last season, 27 on power plays and six shorthanded.
The matchup Tuesday is the first meeting this season between the two teams.
INJURIES: Sabres: Casey Mittelstadt: out (upper body).
Canucks: None listed.
